- Your UI is organized into a "screens" directory (with one composable per main feature/screen) and a "components" directory (for reusable UI chunks like chips, capacity indicators, etc.).
- You use custom themed tokens (NetwinTokens) for consistent spacing, rounded corners, and colors.
- Visual tags/chips use composables like `StatusChip`, which display colored surface chips with bold text and rounded corners.
- PrizeInfo (with icon, rounded style, and label/value layout) is a major chip UI motif in both details and card views, and is the intended way to represent financial info in these contexts.
- InfoChip is also used, sometimes without icons, for compact display of text/value pairs.
- Navigation is managed using `NavGraph`/`NavigationRoutes` for composable screen registration.
- Data/state flows down from ViewModels (for tournaments, registration, profile, auth, etc.).
- Spacing and padding is consistent via tokens, and Compose Material3 is used for theming/material elements.

This context will ensure all future changes and recommendations are consistent with your established architecture, UI hierarchy, and design standards.

